{{Top|leg}}
The '''subelectronic converter''' was a brain implant invented by [[Galactic Empire/Legends|Imperial]] designer [[Nasdra Magrody]] that enabled [[Force-sensitive/Legends|Force-sensitive]] subjects to control [[Droid/Legends|droids]] remotely. One known recipient was [[Irek Ismaren]], who used the implant to control the ''[[Eye of Palpatine]]''.<ref name="JATM">''[[Jedi Academy Training Manual]]''</ref>

The subelectronic converter allowed Ismaren to visualize the programming of computerized devices, and, through the Force, override it. The subelectronic computer allowed him to apply his existing skill in [[Alter Mind]]. It took many months of practice to master.

